claim.claim-text:
1. A die-package socket, comprising:
a socket body;
a cam plate slidingly coupled to the socket body, wherein the cam plate includes a footprint for a semiconductive device, wherein the cam plate includes a plurality of contact slots within the footprint;
a plurality of LGA contacts affixed to the socket body, wherein the plurality of LGA contacts penetrates the cam plate through the plurality of contact slots; and
a cam screw rotatingly coupled to the cam plate and affixed to the socket body;
wherein each LGA contact includes:
an LGA contact body including a tip at a first end of the LGA contact;
a contact paddle at a second end of the LGA contact; and
a plate affixed to the socket body and adjacent the contact paddle.

2. The die-package socket of claim 1, wherein each LGA contact body further includes:
a tip-raising contact-input section adjacent the tip, wherein the tip-raising contact input section has a substantially rectilinear shape;
a tip-lowering contact-input section adjacent the tip-raising input section, wherein the tip-lowering input section has a substantially curvilinear shape.

9. The die-package socket of claim 1, wherein each LGA contact body further includes:
a tip-raising contact-input section adjacent the tip, wherein the tip-raising contact input section has a substantially rectilinear shape; and
a tip-lowering contact-input section adjacent the tip-raising input section, wherein the tip-lowering input section has a substantially curvilinear shape;
wherein the socket body includes an urging seat that is configured to contact the tip-lowering contact-input section;
wherein the cam plate includes an urging wall that is configured to contact the tip-lowering contact-input section; and
wherein the cam plate also includes an urging shoulder that is configured to contact the tip-raising contact-input section.

13. A computer system comprising:
a die-package socket, including:
a socket body;
a cam plate slidingly coupled to the socket body, wherein the cam plate includes a footprint for a semiconductive device, wherein the cam plate includes a plurality of contact slots within the footprint;
a plurality of LGA contacts affixed to the socket body, wherein the plurality of LGA contacts penetrates the cam plate through the plurality of contact slots; and a cam screw rotatingly coupled to the cam plate and affixed to the socket body;
wherein each LGA contact includes:
an LGA contact body including a tip at a first end of the LGA contact;
a contact paddle at a second end of the LGA contact; and
a plate affixed to the socket body and adjacent the contact paddle;
an LGA die package disposed upon the cam plate, wherein the LGA die package includes a die on a first side thereof and plurality of LGA pads on a second side thereof; and
a foundation substrate onto which the LGA-die socket is mounted.
